The paper proposes a deep learning framework for face alignment, which involves using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to learn shape-indexed features and refining the shape via sequential regressions. This work is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which suggests that the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves training deep neural networks, which suggests that it may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed framework is evaluated on several benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
